	<refmeta>
		<refentrytitle>tchk</refentrytitle>
		<manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
	</refmeta>

	<refnamediv>
		<refname>tchk</refname>
		<refpurpose>TenDRA static checker</refpurpose>
	</refnamediv>

	<refsynopsisdiv>
		<cmdsynopsis>
			<command>tchk</command>

			<arg choice="opt"><replaceable>options</replaceable></arg>
			<arg choice="plain"><replaceable>files</replaceable></arg>
		</cmdsynopsis>
	</refsynopsisdiv>

	<refsection>
		<title>Description</title>

		<para>&tchk; is the stand-alone TenDRA Static Program Checker.
			It is more fully documented in &tchk.doc;.</para>

		<para>&tchk; is equivalent to <command>tcc -ch</command> except that it
			does not allow all the options allowed by &tcc;.
			A complete list of the options allowed can be printed using the
			<option>-query</option> option.</para>
	</refsection>

